('tld024','us',
'<p>The <strong>.us</strong> domain is the official ccTLD for the <strong>United States of America</strong>. It is managed by <strong>Neustar (now GoDaddy)</strong> on behalf of the US government.</p>',
'<p>Delegated in 1985, .us was initially used by U.S. government and local entities. In 2002, it was opened for broader registration. It is popular for local businesses and government agencies wanting to emphasize American identity.</p>',
'<p>Used by:</p><ul><li><strong>U.S. businesses and brands</strong></li><li><strong>Local government agencies</strong></li><li><strong>American-focused services</strong></li></ul>',
'[]',
'<p>Restricted to <strong>U.S. citizens, residents, and entities</strong>. Cost: approximately <strong>$8–$15/year</strong>.</p>',
1,0,'system',NOW()),

('tld025','eu',
'<p>The <strong>.eu</strong> domain is the official ccTLD for the <strong>European Union</strong>. It represents European identity, trust, and GDPR compliance.</p>',
'<p>Launched in 2006 by <strong>EURid</strong> (European Registry for Internet Domains), .eu quickly amassed over 3 million registrations. It is one of the most successful regional TLDs.</p>',
'<p>Used by:</p><ul><li><strong>EU-based businesses</strong></li><li><strong>EU institutions and organizations</strong></li><li><strong>Pan-European projects</strong></li><li><strong>Companies targeting European customers</strong></li></ul>',
'[{"name":"EU Parliament","url":"europarl.europa.eu"}]',
'<p>Restricted to <strong>EU citizens, residents, and organizations</strong> based in EU member states. Cost: approximately <strong>$10–$15/year</strong>.</p>',
1,0,'system',NOW()),

('tld026','cc',
'<p>The <strong>.cc</strong> domain is the ccTLD for the <strong>Cocos (Keeling) Islands</strong>, but is widely used as a generic domain — interpreted as "company," "commerce," or "credit card." It is a popular two-letter alternative to .com.</p>',
